{
  "texts": [
    "How does this approach compare to existing research methods?",
    "Laboratory and field experiments remain the gold standard for testing theoretical predictions (Chatterji et al., 2016).",
    "These experiments are conducted on the actual subjects of interest (i.e., humans or organizations), so observations represent the \"ground truth.\"",
    "This is not true for experiments using LLMs, which can show idiosyncratic behavior (Mohammadi, 2024) or rationality biases (Hagendorff, 2024).",
    "However, lab and field experiments are typically conducted when there is already an established theory, which has generated key predictions that are ready to be tested (Card et al., 2011)."
  ]
}